# UIPress.PressType.pageUp

**Case**

A constant that represents the page up button.

## Declaration

```swift
case pageUp
```

## Discussion

Add gesture recognizers for [doc://com.apple.uikit/documentation/UIKit/UIPress/PressType/pageDown] and [doc://com.apple.uikit/documentation/UIKit/UIPress/PressType/pageUp] to navigate content in your app.

In an electronic program guide, select the item above the current one in response to [doc://com.apple.uikit/documentation/UIKit/UIPress/PressType/upArrow], and display the previous screen of items in response to [doc://com.apple.uikit/documentation/UIKit/UIPress/PressType/pageUp]. While your content plays, change the channel when your app receives [doc://com.apple.uikit/documentation/UIKit/UIPress/PressType/pageUp] or [doc://com.apple.uikit/documentation/UIKit/UIPress/PressType/pageDown].

For more details on browsing multichannel content, see [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/TVServices/providing-channel-navigation].
